<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,1369,1937]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1622,1648]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Remarks</emphasis>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H." box="[481,623,1622,1648]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref72204" refString="Gore, R. H. (1982) Porcellanid crabs from the coasts of Mexico and Central America (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 363, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.363" type="journal article" year="1982">Gore (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[637,767,1622,1648]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichotus">
<emphasis box="[637,767,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. trichotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extremely rare species, previously known from only 
<specimenCount box="[151,325,1658,1684]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
, in addition to 
<specimenCount box="[493,659,1658,1684]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
examined by this author. 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[949,1086,1658,1685]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[1206,1334,1658,1684]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichotus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1334,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. trichotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the very similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[293,453,1695,1720]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[293,453,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the P1 fingers; the presence of plumose setae on the carapace front and P1âP4; and the absence of pleopods in males. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H." box="[776,912,1730,1756]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref72204" refString="Gore, R. H. (1982) Porcellanid crabs from the coasts of Mexico and Central America (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 363, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.363" type="journal article" year="1982">Gore (1982)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[1030,1156,1730,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichotus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1156,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. trichotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[1278,1436,1731,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1731,1756]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[200,377,1766,1792]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinidactylus">
<emphasis box="[200,377,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. spinidactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the epimeral plate formula, which the author found to be âboth distinctive and consistent, comprising a single large plate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[535,663,1802,1828]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichotus">
<emphasis box="[535,663,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. trichotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one large and one small plate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[1045,1222,1802,1828]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinidactylus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1222,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. spinidactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and one large and several smaller fragments in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[477,638,1839,1864]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[477,638,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
â. Unfortunately, the 
<specimenCount box="[877,1043,1838,1864]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[1082,1210,1838,1864]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichotus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1210,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. trichotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from RÃ­o Mar were not photographed alive, likely due to the speciesâ resemblance with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[930,1092,1875,1900]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Pachycheles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[930,1092,1875,1900]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was also found at this locality (see above).
</paragraph>
